    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79600 Reservations/10–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 5, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>620. Father Laberge, newly appointed American priest in Moscow, is leaving
                    Washington October 10, via ATC<note n="9" xml:id="d876fn9">Air Transport
                        Command.</note> for Moscow. SovEmb has assured him of onward air
                    transportation from Berlin. Please assist Father Laberge to arrange for
                    reservations on Soviet plane.<note n="10" xml:id="d876fn10">Father Laberge
                        arrived in Moscow on October 26. After turning over the duties of his office
                        to his successor, Father Braun left Moscow on December 27, in the airplane
                        of Secretary of State James F. Byrnes, who had been attending the Conference
                        of Foreign Ministers held there December 16–26, 1945.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow as no. 2101.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
